Sec. 78.043. NOTICE OF CONTROL MEASURES. The chairman of the
board shall give written notice to each person who holds title to or
possesses land located in the district of:
(1) the control measures in effect on the person's land;
and
(2) information necessary to enable the person to carry out
the measures.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1214, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

